API Overview
Stop letting non-compliant nurse hires sit in your pipeline. The Nurse License Verification API returns real-time RN, APRN, and LVN license status from official state nursing board portals across 31 states in a single call. Replace hours of manual board-by-board lookups with a structured JSON response your credentialing or staffing workflow can act on in milliseconds.
Compliance and revenue are the same problem. A travel nurse with a lapsed Texas RN sitting on a contracted shift is a clawback waiting to happen. A psychiatric NP placed in New York without an active 040 specialty registration is a Joint Commission audit finding. A staffing agency that submits a credentialing packet with stale license data eats the rebill. This API exists so the verification step in front of those failure modes is a function call instead of a person manually loading 31 different state board websites.
Coverage, stated honestly:
	•	Full RN and APRN verification in New York (16 NP specialties including Psychiatry, code 040) and California (RN, NP, and LVN by license type).
	•	RN-only verification in Florida, Texas, and 28 additional states.
	•	31 states confirmed live and covered by nightly smoke tests.
	•	19 states are excluded by structural blockers we will not work around silently. Cloudflare WAF, FormShield, Incapsula, reCAPTCHA, and similar bot-mitigation layers prevent reliable scraping. We would rather you self-select on accurate scope than discover a gap in production.
What you get back on every verify call:
	•	License number, full name, license type, status (Active, Inactive, Expired, Suspended, etc.), issue date, expiration date, and discipline data when the state board exposes it.
	•	A single normalized response shape across all 31 states. State boards present this data in 31 different ways. We do not pass that mess to you.
	•	Source URL pointing at the underlying state board record, so your audit trail terminates at a public, citable government source.
When to use which endpoint:
	•	Use /verify when you have a license number. This is the fast path, hits the state board directly, and returns the full record. Hard recommendation for batch credentialing workflows.
	•	Use /search when you only have a name. Returns matching records you then resolve down with /verify. Slower (some states require CAPTCHA solves) and not all states return complete fields on search.
Common integration patterns:
	•	Pre-hire credentialing: call /verify on every license number in an applicant packet before the recruiter ever opens the file.
	•	Ongoing roster monitoring: re-verify your active nurse roster on a 30 or 60 day cadence to catch lapses before the next pay period.
	•	Pre-shift compliance gates: insert a /verify call into your scheduling system so an expired license cannot be assigned to a covered shift.
	•	Audit prep: pull a fresh verification record on every active credential 7 days before a Joint Commission, NCQA, or payer delegation audit.
