Quick Start
The Nurse License Verification API returns real-time license status (Active, Inactive, Expired, Suspended) from official state nursing board portals. Authenticate every request with the standard RapidAPI headers X-RapidAPI-Key and X-RapidAPI-Host. The Free (BASIC) tier includes 50 requests per month and full access to all 31 supported states, which is sufficient for evaluation and integration testing. When you have a license number, use POST /verify; when you only have a name, use GET /search.
Authentication
All requests are authenticated via RapidAPI's standard gateway headers. No separate API key is required beyond your RapidAPI key.
X-RapidAPI-Key: YOUR_RAPIDAPI_KEY
X-RapidAPI-Host: nurse-license-verification.p.rapidapi.com
Your RapidAPI key is available in your RapidAPI dashboard. The host header must match the listing exactly.
Endpoints
POST /verify
Verify a nurse license by license number and state. Returns the full structured license record including license number, full name, license type (RN, NP, APRN, LVN, CN), status, issue and expiration dates, and discipline data when the state board exposes it. This is the fast path and the recommended primary endpoint for credentialing workflows. Expect 200ms to 1.5s on warm states, longer on states with CAPTCHA challenges.
curl example:
curl -X POST 'https://nurse-license-verification.p.rapidapi.com/verify' \
  -H 'X-RapidAPI-Key: YOUR_RAPIDAPI_KEY' \
  -H 'X-RapidAPI-Host: nurse-license-verification.p.rapidapi.com' \
  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
  -d '{"state": "TX", "license_number": "751234"}'
JavaScript fetch example:
const response = await fetch('https://nurse-license-verification.p.rapidapi.com/verify', {
  method: 'POST',
  headers: {
    'X-RapidAPI-Key': 'YOUR_RAPIDAPI_KEY',
    'X-RapidAPI-Host': 'nurse-license-verification.p.rapidapi.com',
    'Content-Type': 'application/json'
  },
  body: JSON.stringify({ state: 'TX', license_number: '751234' })
});
const data = await response.json();
