Common Errors
	•	unsupported_state: Returned when the requested state is not in the supported set (19 states are excluded by structural blockers like Cloudflare WAF, FormShield, Incapsula, or reCAPTCHA). Call /states to see the current supported list before retrying.
	•	400 invalid_input: Missing or malformed required fields (state must be a two-letter code, license_number must be present). The error body indicates which field failed validation. Fix the request payload and resubmit.
	•	404 not_found: The state board returned no matching record for the supplied license number. Confirm the license number and state with the caller, or fall back to /search by name.
	•	429 rate_limited: You exceeded your tier's per-minute or per-month request quota. Back off and retry, or upgrade your tier in the RapidAPI Monetize tab.
	•	5xx upstream_unavailable: The state board portal is down, in maintenance, or rate-limiting our scraper. State boards do not publish maintenance schedules. Retry with exponential backoff; persistent failures should be reported to contact@licenseapi.dev.
